text.tspan: Do people with abnormal chromosomes have the same probability of
having a criminal record as those with normal chromosomes?
There is moderately strong evidence that the probability of having a
criminal record is different for those with and without the abnormality.
4124 Danish males were classified as having a criminal record or not, based on
penal registers. Each was also classified as having a normal male XY chromosome
or one of the abnormalities XYY or XXY.
